<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1436,1518,1724]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Karyotype: 2n = 35–36 and FN = 40. Autosomal complement: three small metacentric pairs, and 14 acrocentric pairs (three large, one medium, and the remaining small decreasing in size). The medium-sized element was apparently involved in a Robertsonian polymorphism, with heterozygous individuals found at two different localities, all others localities were homozygous for the acrocentric condition (
<tableCitation box="[877,963,1661,1687]" captionStart="TABLE 6" captionStartId="30.[151,239,525,551]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="TABLE 6. Karyotype data of genus Neacomys. Species, diploid (2n) and fundamental (FN) numbers, collection localities, geographic coordinates and reference." pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Table 6</tableCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[975,1042,1661,1688]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="32.[151,250,1103,1127]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,189,1072]" captionTargetId="figure-17@32.[151,1436,181,1079]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURE 7. Distribution of diploid and fundamental number of karyotyped specimens of genus Neacomys. (♦) N. dubosti; (☆) N. macedoruizi; (r) N. minutus; (○) N. musseri; (■) N. paracou; (l) N. rosalindae; (ê) N. spinosus; (◊) Neacomys sp.; (□) Neacomys sp. 1; (▲) Neacomys sp. 2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423633" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4423633/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Sex chromosomes: X, a mediumsmall metacentric; Y, a small acrocentric (
